  INSERT INTO brain_dumps (user_id, title, answers, time_spent, answered_count, created_at) VALUES
  (target_user_id, 'Prove that the testimonials that Andrea is receiving are ...', '["Prove that the testimonials that Andrea is receiving are from real people and not fake.", "World we live in today: people are more and more suspicious of deep fakes and AI-generated content. Using a profile picture alongside a quote that gives people a QR code to watch a full testimonials video reinforces that these are real people with real experiences, real work with Andrea", "A clean profile picture of a neutral / slight smile that is close to the original facial expressions that Hussain is showing. Background can be cleaned up, but everything about Hussain needs to stay as accurate as possible. ", "An image that looks highly edited/Photoshopped/over-idealized.", "We don''t have a profile picture for him. What we''ve been using is a screenshot from the video.", "", ""]'::jsonb, '04:34', 5, '2026-04-01T19:15:45.456Z'::timestamptz),
  (target_user_id, 'When our ICP Scott sees our posts on LinkedIn, we want hi...', '["When our ICP Scott sees our posts on LinkedIn, we want him to feel like the \"Weekly Team Meeting Health Checkup & Diagnostic\" is a no brainer and will want to sign up for it right away. ", "ACP Enlightening is actively seeking 2-3 new clients. If we don''t help facilitate this, it erodes the value of what 8 SIGNAL is doing for her. ", "\"Weekly Team Meeting Health Checkup & Diagnostic\" He''s a tongue twister causes confusion. We need a new name for this core offer that is memorable, clear, and drives value.  The new name should also include three to five short benefit statements. ", "Replacing one tongue twister with another, diluting the value, making it confusing to understand what it is that they''re getting.", "Previously put together a slide deck that Andrea at ACP Enlighten really likes: https://docs.google.com/presentation/d/1WeStDaCPtCw5CLYJFQMq1jF-P6ngpHshLMjhpuPbFWg/edit?slide=id.p1#slide=id.p1", "Review the slide deck. Investigate best-performing sales copy formulas. Review Alex Hormozi''s $100 million offer formula. Generate five naming options. After I select one of the options, then begin writing the five short benefit statements to support this offer.", ""]'::jsonb, '12:14', 6, '2026-04-01T14:39:56.630Z'::timestamptz),
  (target_user_id, 'LinkedIn content strategy playbook for Forrest''s brand', '["Increase authority and perception of value for Forrest''s brand through his LinkedIn posts.", "Wants to be the go-to trainer for fractional COOs and fractional integrators. Wants to become a recognized authority within the EOS community for helping others grow.", "A detailed strategy and playbook that informs the content team:\n- How to identify topics to create content for LinkedIn posts\n- The variety of content type\n- An ongoing schedule for when to type which types of posts\n- Outlining which posts to repurpose and which ones not to and why or why not\n- Clear style and tone of voice that is aligned with Forrest''s personality and/or his brand\n- Copywriting checklist for an editor or the writer to go through to make sure that they are on point. For example, guidance and direction on: the opening hook, calls to action, when and where to use URLs, et cetera", "- Too much fluff and filler content within the playbook.\n- Vague, unclear, or overly generalized guidance and direction.\n- A playbook that doesn''t get used because it overwhelms the team that will be using it.\n- It cannot be overly prescriptive. A creative should feel like they''re given really clear direction but still have the freedom to express their creativity.", "Forrest''s team is using Hootsuite to schedule posts in order to avoid conflict with his copywriter. She posts certain days in the morning, and he posts whatever is on his mind in the afternoons. He''s so good with his LinkedIn content strategy that he has a lot of engagement, and people want to know how he pulls it off. However, his current strategy is just to post consistently and post often. Beyond that, he feels like he''s just going with his gut. He is also beginning to post very consistently on YouTube, and he is being interviewed for podcasts where he is increasing his reach.", "Review his two websites, Derr Consulting and Fractionator Playbooks. Analyze his LinkedIn account, his YouTube channel, his Facebook and Instagram pages.\nTake a look at his marketing blueprint.\nIdentify what strategies work for LinkedIn today and what things won''t work.\nBuild out the playbook into logical and sequential parts.", "Building out a full content strategy for LinkedIn is not something that I have experience with, so I''m unsure as to what might be some of the potential pitfalls. I may not be able to recognize when the output is very confident yet very wrong."]'::jsonb, '10:00', 7, '2026-03-26T23:12:29.290Z'::timestamptz),
  (target_user_id, 'Remove friction, eliminate confusion, and build up excite...', '["Remove friction, eliminate confusion, and build up excitement for Ben to want to work with us.", "We need to generate sales to shore up our war chest bank account and need more opportunities to practice doing the 90-day sprint that is value-based and not time-based.", "A fully custom proposal using our 90-day sprint proposal template. Output as a markdown file that can be copy-pasted into a Google Doc. Model after the other proposals that have been generated in this Claude account, where it summarizes our previous meeting and the things we heard. ", "People are sick and tired of AI slop, and there are clear patterns that we are learning to detect when someone heavily relied on AI to generate proposals, content, etc., versus when there was actual intent and human thinking. For example: Forced negation and staccato sentence. “Its not just.. it’s…” ABSOLUTELY NO EM DASHES!!! Use commas instead of em dashes. Using too much information instead of being clear, succinct, and to the point \n\n", "Reference the discovery call that I had with Ben. Ben is the video storyteller behind Forrest''s content on LinkedIn. Ben will be attending the EOS conference in April, and we will have an opportunity to meet each other. He has a YouTube channel with over 100,000 subscribers that''s focused on tech. The YouTube channel is not for his new intended audience that he''s trying to reach.", "Review the Fireflies transcript.\nTake a look at his YouTube channel.\nReview his LinkedIn page.\nResearch Ben Kaiser''s digital footprint in addition to his YouTube channel or LinkedIn page. \nDo all these things before writing the proposal.", "I''m still waiting on Ben for a descriptor of the demographics of his ideal client profile, so you will have to infer based on the transcript from our call."]'::jsonb, '15:00', 7, '2026-03-24T19:05:44.365Z'::timestamptz),
  (target_user_id, 'Create a brand that stands out and looks fresh and classi...', '["Create a brand that stands out and looks fresh and classic at the same time in order to attract  the attention of religious organizations. ", "It''s important to make a first impression, wow clients, and make them feel confident in the company, We Adore Thee.", "A complete brand guideline that includes everything: fonts, colors, feel, web elements, print elements. This brand guideline is a step before developing the website. Also, he''d be used for any other collateral that''s going to be created, or as a set of instructions to use with AI in order to give it good guidance. The brand style guide should itself exemplify and be a visual representation of what the brand stands for and how it should look. ", "Wrong would look like a client looking at this and feeling like it''s outdated, not fresh, not eye-catching, and just aesthetically unpleasing. It should not give the feeling of \"Oh, I''ve seen one, so I''ve seen them all.\" It should give more of the feeling of \"Wow, this is a really interesting and unique way of showing a brand guideline.\" ", "We''re entering into a space that''s very crowded with very bad looking stuff and very good looking stuff. That space is the world of Catholic and religious design. What this company needs to show is that it can rise above all of that.\n", "Pieces this needs to use will be:\n- the display of brand colors\n- fonts\n- situations\n- how it treats everything from paragraph text down to buttons\n- what the do''s and don''ts of use of the logo would be\n- what a headline looks like\n- what a sub-headline looks like\n- what a sub-sub-headline looks like\n- what paragraph text looks like\n- the mix of weights and colors within those fonts\n- the type of imagery that should or should not be used\nWhile we''re working through this process, I would like to start with color palette. From there, go to font and font choices, and then from there go to texture and layout. On each of those steps, I''d like to be presented with various options that I can then choose from and move forward or give suggestions on how they can be changed. ", "I would love to see if it''s possible a mix of classic design with neuomorphic design with elements that make Catholicism and Catholic cathedrals beautiful. That''s going to take a lot of mixing of different styles to see it both futuristically and traditionally, but I think it can be done. I just can''t picture it in my head right now."]'::jsonb, '14:28', 7, '2026-03-21T19:41:31.862Z'::timestamptz),
  (target_user_id, 'Support Andrea''s conversations with prospects so they hav...', '["Support Andrea''s conversations with prospects so they have a quick reference document they can print out or save to their computer so that she can stay front and center with her ICP. ", "This flier sits in a very important spot in her sales and follow up process.", "2-Page flier design that is consistent with her brand identity. The final version needs to be in canva so that Andrea or anyone else can make edits to the file on an ongoing basis. It''s okay if the flyer is a little on the dense side of things when it comes to the content. As long as there is a good visual hierarchy and flow to the information. ", "This has veered off course if there is information that is added that was not included in the Google Doc. A finished product that is very cramped. If you see that it''s just too much information for a two-page flyer, rather than trying to cram it all in, please bring the issue up along with 1-3 recommendations on how  solve the issue. ", "", "If there are no issues while designing, please notify Andrea and me in the ACP Slack channel, letting us know when it''s completed.", "I''m not sure what happened with the center of influence flyer that was previously done in Canva, but we were unable to access it and had to make a copy of that so that Andrea could access and make edits. "]'::jsonb, '07:42', 6, '2026-03-19T20:48:25.256Z'::timestamptz),
  (target_user_id, 'Give prospects a better insight into who Ruben is so that...', '["Give prospects a better insight into who Ruben is so that they want to have a conversation with us and turn into a lead that will want to hire 8 SIGNAL. \n\nAlign Ruben''s LinkedIn profile headline to the LinkedIn cold outreach campaign that is about to launch. \n", "We want to be aligned with who are communicating with, be relatable, attract potential clients in t he most effective way possible. We weren''t doing this well before. It matters because they can more readily turn into a qualified lead. ", "Polished headline that is optimized in length and style for LinkedIn. It needs to be clear, concise, in the 8 SIGNAL tone, and give a quick snapshot of who Ruben is. ", "Too wordy. Long. Impersonal. Jargon. Unclear. Read like it was written by AI. Exceed character limits available.  No more em dashes --- please! Vanilla and not memorable. Follow proper tone and tense. ", "Style guide link\nWebsite link\nTone and voice link\nMarketing blueprint link\nWe tried this other thing before, we''re pivoting based on advice from that person (add notes to inform this) ", "Get clear on best performing LinkedIn profile headlines\nExplain it\nGenerate 3-5 options\nExplain the pros and cons of each option ", "This is a very small task (Write LinkeIn headline) with high visibility and high impact."]'::jsonb, '15:00', 7, '2026-03-18T22:09:59.741Z'::timestamptz),
  (target_user_id, 'Create an opportunity for a sales discovery call or sales...', '["Create an opportunity for a sales discovery call or sales follow-up conversation between Scott, the ICP, and Andrea. ", "Scott is always busy, moves fast, and doesn''t always have the patience to take the time to find what He needs. He wants to find it quickly, he wants it to be readily accessible, and he wants to take action on it now. Otherwise, the window of opportunity gets lost with him. This document is important because it''s something that he could readily search for in his email, or, if he''s interested enough, would have already gotten an email and saved this PDF somewhere easy to find on his laptop. In some scenarios, he might actually just print it out and have it on his desk. ", "Format: Single-page flyer (one page only, not two). Must be visually clean with strong visual hierarchy — avoid the \"cluttered\" feel of the current flyer. Andrea wants it to feel consistent with the new brand style (the deep blue background was preferred over the grey — she described it as giving more \"strength\" and \"presence\"). \nReference/Inspiration: An EOS Implementer flyer that Andrea found and shared. She liked it because despite having a lot of content, it''s structured so the eye flows naturally (headline → key points → supporting info) without feeling overwhelming. The current ACP flyer has more visual clutter and lacks that hierarchy. See that PDF here: https://drive.google.com/file/d/1RXEWST5le1DhbwALG9XG2NUOzV2choC3/view?usp=sharing\nContent Elements to Include:\n\nHero section — A clear statement of what ACP does and the end result/outcome for the client. Think: \"What do I do?\" and \"What''s the final result?\"\nDifferentiators (Unique Value Propositions) — The key things that set ACP apart from other integrators/consultants. These should be prominent.\nCore Values — Can be included in a smaller/secondary placement, but Andrea wants them visible somewhere on the flyer.\nCertification/Credential Logos — Andrea considers these a major differentiator. There are 6 logos total. They should be displayed in grey/monochrome so they don''t visually overpower the design. The two most important logos are EOS and CPA — EOS goes on the far left, CPA on the far right, with the remaining four in between. (Note: the Masterclass logo is not needed; also one specific EOS logo cannot be used — confirm which version is permissible.)\nContact Information — Andrea''s contact details.\nA Testimonial Quote — Ruben specifically mentioned incorporating a testimonial quote into the flyer before the meeting wrapped.\nCall to Action (CTA) — Two CTAs were discussed:\n\nPrimary: \"Schedule your first call\" (or similar language to encourage direct contact)\nSecondary: Something like \"Visit website to watch testimonial videos\" — directing people to the page with the video testimonials. Andrea feels strongly that the testimonial videos are what push prospects over the edge to make contact, since the ICP (\"Scott\") tends to be distrustful and seeing real people with real names builds credibility.", "Cluttered information. Lack of visual hierarchy just through the typography alone.  No clear call to action and poor visibility of the call to action. Here''s an example of a PDF that has as much or less information than the previous example and yet looks busier and more difficult to get to the information that is most important. https://drive.google.com/file/d/1RXEWST5le1DhbwALG9XG2NUOzV2choC3/view?usp=sharing", "ACP''s Proven Process: https://docs.google.com/document/d/1PKBfsmIRPtLxCeIl7eGG7V9l1q4BlQ36oG1k5O-KOWI/edit?usp=sharing\nACP''s Core Values and Three Uniques: https://docs.google.com/document/d/1qRfcigTO_n_S83tcnQ-ZUkWsZHrf5BmN1opocuM7yKw/edit?usp=sharing\nACP''s Website: https://acpenlightening.com/\nACP''s testimonials compilation video: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=5RSkfTQVAYE\n", "1. Review all the available resources.\n2. Find outside third-party resources that would support this project.\n3. Create a markdown document with all the copy Flyer \n4. Create a graphic design in PDF format to help see the visuals", ""]'::jsonb, '15:00', 6, '2026-03-17T19:50:20.236Z'::timestamptz),
  (target_user_id, 'Leverage the rebranding and the new testimonials compilat...', '["Leverage the rebranding and the new testimonials compilation video that were both just launched to build awareness and create outreach opportunity on LinkedIn for Andrea. ", "As a solo entrepreneur and fractional COO, client acquisition is incredibly important for Andrea''s livelihood when she needs to fill one of her client slots.  ", "A marketing campaign that clearly explains the reasoning behind how the campaign is structured and why is it structured that way (strategy). A series of LinkedIn posts written in a format that optimizes for engagement on LinkedIn that have a strong emphasis on storytelling and strong hooks to engage her ICP and COIs (centers of influence) and include visual recommendations for each LinkedIn post (collateral1). Email sequence that she can send out to her current list, which includes former clients, potential clients, and centers of influence.", "Posts that get little to no engagement. Emails that don''t get opened. Having a lack of clear calls to action. Written in a tone and style that does not connect with ACP''s ideal client profile. ", "Previously wrote out an entire plan. Andrea was not happy about it because she wanted to showcase the compilation video and reference the new website on every post. I pushed back on that, saying that the campaign was not about the rebrand or the video itself, but instead it was about using it as an opportunity to have people reach out to her to ask about her services and if she has any days available to take on clients. I told her that I would revisit the existing campaign, look for opportunities to weave in the testimonial video and the rebranding of the website without making that front and center. She was very happy with that. \n\nResources: \nwebsite: https://acpenlightening.com/\ncompilation video: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=5RSkfTQVAYE\nlinkedin profile: https://www.linkedin.com/in/andreacperales/\n\nHere''s the original series of posts and sequence of emails: https://docs.google.com/document/d/1NMcf3YJNTV9j-1O8W1MyoYoVO7DS0ssETVXkA4xpzhs/edit?tab=t.pnvr8x8ncrsu ", "Campaign \"format\"\n- md file, not a docx file\n- explanation of how the campaign is structured and why\n- collateral for linkedin\n- collateral for emails\n- proposed timeline of when to schedule each post/email", ""]'::jsonb, '15:00', 6, '2026-03-17T17:35:32.599Z'::timestamptz),
  (target_user_id, 'EOS Conference attendees who are in Forrest''s network who...', '["EOS Conference attendees who are in Forrest''s network who are COOs and Integrators to sign up to join his free AMA on Wednesday, April 22, 2pm CT.  ", "Forrest is building his brand around being the COO that other COOs go to for training and coaching on how to be a fractional COO. He''s been developing his brand and recently launched https://fractionatorplaybooks.com/.  He''s very active on LinkedIn and has quite a following: https://www.linkedin.com/in/forrestkderr/recent-activity/all/.  His original website is still https://derrconsulting.com/. We recently took his wife on as a client as well and will be launching her website soon. ", "A series of LinkedIn post drafts with recommended/suggested graphics/images/etc that he can start publishing so that his audience is excited to meet him in person and attend his AMA in April. Follow LinkedIn content best practices that maximize visibility. Make it direct response style copy that is very friendly, down to earth, approachable all while exuding confidence that Forrest gets sh** done and doesn''t waste anyone''s time. ", "Copy that doesn''t hook the reader, or uses heavy-handed sales tactics to try and hook the reader in. There''s no story. Most importantly, this failed if people don''t sign up for the AMA or if they aren''t going to the conference, aren''t inspired to share the posts on behalf of Forrest. ", "Forrest has a small list of under 200 contacts in hubspot. He offers a playbook that people can purchase. His lead magnet is  the AMA, the entry point offer is the playbook, and his next core offer is 1-1 monthly coaching. ", "The marketing blueprint needs to be understood well. It goes deep into the ICP and the messaging to attract that ICP. A brief strategy write up is needed to explain as to why the LinkedIn campaign is being mapped out as it is.  The markdown document needs to be clear, concise, and direct so that a writer, editor, or social media person can get a fast understanding of what needs to be done, why, and then be able to access the materials that are going to get published without getting confused as to what should be published and what is scripter information about the campaign. ", ""]'::jsonb, '15:00', 6, '2026-03-16T20:52:24.494Z'::timestamptz),
  (target_user_id, 'Outcome: a workflow to launch a detailed marketing bluepr...', '["Outcome: a workflow to launch a detailed marketing blueprint for clients by using agents, followed by a custom website built with claude and/or google ai studio and then deployed to vercel", "Entrepreneurs are beginning to use AI without any real history of expertise in the area of marketing and design. This means that companies like 8signal are being replaced even if the quality of work is not good, only fair. Additionally, clients are expecting work to be delivered faster now with the advent of AI. Being able to create marketing blueprints and a first concept web design in record speed is critical to maintain a competitive advantage in the marketplace. ", "A detailed workflow that reverse engineers our approach to building a marketing blueprint and fills the gaps for building out a web custom website. Understanding which parts of that workflow can be handed to an AI agent and which ones need human intervention. Their instructions or access to resources to help implement the workflow and the building of the AI agents required for deployment ", "A workflow that heavily relies on human intervention. Needing to dig further and re-prompt multiple times just to get desired outcomes from the workflow. The finished product, marketing blueprints and web designs, that look cookie-cutter or clones of each other. ", "We have an entire process for building out marketing blueprints where we get some of the basic demographic information from the client. From there, we build out a detailed marketing blueprint. Here is a linked example of the most recent one. \n\nhttps://docs.google.com/document/d/1G8ka_nRy1Mng9sHV20mjtzqaw5aCkfdF8PTDjCKm5AU/edit?tab=t.0\n\nCurrent tools we use: \n - Claude\n- Google AI Studio\n- Google Gemini\n- Google Docs\n- Asana\n- Slack\n- Gmail\n- github\n- vercel\n- previously built websites on wordpress\n\nHere come some instructions for building out the marketing blueprint. However, this currently needs a lot of back and forth internally with re-prompting and a review of the final marketing blueprint with the client for additional edits and revisions. \n\nWe have a person on the team who is a creative director and fractional CMO to help guide the quality of work. \n\nThe constraint we currently have is that pulling on Vercel makes it super fast; however, it makes it difficult to set up the website for ongoing SEO. We don''t yet have a structure in place for how to launch websites that will have ongoing blog content on a weekly basis. ", "All projects start with marketing blueprint. For the marketing blueprint, we need some demographic information from the client. That information gets turned into a detailed marketing blueprint that identifies constraints, desired outcomes, key purchase drivers. We use that information to create a before and after transformation grid that helps inform what the brand messaging should be. From there, we identify brands outside of the industry that do a good job appealing to that particular ICP. That begins to drive the brand recommendations in terms of personality, character, and style of the brand. We recommend colors and fonts for that. ", "Don''t have a person that knows how to do technical set up, so it falls on me as the founder to get it all done. That either pulls me away from the current duties and responsibilities that I have, or I start initiatives like this, but they never go anywhere. We end up with a lot of half-built bridges, or in worst-case scenarios, I don''t finish these initiatives and I neglect current workload. "]'::jsonb, '15:00', 7, '2026-03-16T15:04:10.280Z'::timestamptz),
  (target_user_id, 'Build out a sales playbook SOP for 8 SIGNAL', '["I need to build out a sales playbook that will be used as an SOP to train new salespeople and for accountability and ongoing training with existing salespeople.", "This playbook is very important because everything that we currently have documented is in multiple documents or apps and requires a lot of digging and extra work in order to put all the pieces together of what a sales process looks like from prospect to client.", "It needs to include:\n- the stages in the sales pipeline\n- the different steps required inside of each stage\n- talking points, scripts, and templates\n- a reference guide for what sales collateral and tools are available to the salesperson to help them in the sales process\n\nIt needs to be concise and friendly and anyone that''s going through this playbook will feel like everything is clear. It needs to be written in such a way that they will not feel overwhelmed. This playbook should allow them to do at least 80% of the job of being a salesperson at 8 SIGNAL without a lot of hand-holding or ongoing guidance.", "This task will be considered a failure if I show it to the leadership team and they have a difficult time understanding it. If they are unable to follow the different stages of our sales process. It will also be a failure if a salesperson can''t quickly identify where a particular prospect is in the sales process, why they are in that stage. What steps are necessary for them to go through within that stage and what available resources do they have in order to help the prospect move to the next stage?", "https://app.asana.com/1/8021729341935/project/8021729341937/task/1212840822875451\nThis is my quarterly rock. I just listed the milestones for this rock. The attached screenshot is the current sales pipeline stages that we''re using. I need help figuring out what stages we should actually be using and how to name them.\n\nhttps://docs.google.com/document/d/1eguwifWTdDbDkifwuQIGnSV7wGLC8Jdx-6uVnKEDd4g/edit?tab=t.0#heading=h.6eyq31nez5ei\nIn this Google document, I have a ton of notes that I''ve been capturing as I go through sales training with Sales Velocity. They recommend what the sales pipeline should look like.\n\nhttps://docs.google.com/document/d/1obrzK_816Kat9krZlpW2TpVNghrSd4GOxapO-VQ5MIA/edit\nThis document has 14 or more different tabs in it and it has loads of content of things that we''ve done, tried, put in place, are currently using, and stopped using. This started out as our original sales playbook and it evolved into this giant monstrosity of information that is difficult to sift through.", "I''m gonna need help figuring out what all the pieces are for this task. I''m having a really hard time seeing the big picture of how to lay this out.", "I would say that the greatest challenge for this task is that I am not a sales manager. I am an inexperienced salesperson with very little formal training."]'::jsonb, '12:00', 7, '2026-03-12T22:15:24.144Z'::timestamptz),
  (target_user_id, 'Invite LinkedIn connections to meet at EOS conference', '["I would like to invite my connections on LinkedIn through a series of LinkedIn posts to schedule a time for us to meet if they are also attending the EOS conference at the end of April.", "The reason this is important is because I want to get the most out of the conference by making in-person connections and building referral opportunities, and to deepen relationships with centers of influence that I''m already in conversations with. During these scheduled meetings, I would like to discuss how we might be able to collaborate and offer them ways to truly serve their clients.", "What I''m looking for is beautifully crafted, engaging posts that include recommendations for graphics or videos to use, that points people to a calendar booking link. Length and tone needs to be optimized for today''s most engaging content on LinkedIn, while still keeping the Ruben Reynolds lite personality. Have a strong hook use storytelling.", "Can''t sound salesy or in your face. Also should not sound canned.", "I''ve already begun developing a top 20 list of people that I want to do in-depth touch points on a regular basis. One of those people is Forrest. He has been to this conference several times before, and he has offered to help me out and guide me through how to get the most out of networking at this conference.", "This question is the one I struggle with the most and don''t have a good answer for it.", "The hard part for me about this is that I don''t know that I''ve cracked the code on what good, engaging copy that gets people to like, comment, and take action looks like."]'::jsonb, '10:00', 7, '2026-03-12T22:10:56.257Z'::timestamptz);
